<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="109" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="20" pageNumber="109">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="20" pageNumber="109">
The description of 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Stipa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Stipa virlettii" order="Poales" pageId="20" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="virlettii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="109">Stipa virlettii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Type: 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="109">Virlet 1376</emphasis>
from San Luis de 
<normalizedToken originalValue="PotosÃ­">Potosi</normalizedToken>
, Mexico) appears to be a mixture of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kunth" authorityYear="1816" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Stipa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Stipa mucronata" order="Poales" pageId="20" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mucronata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="109">Stipa mucronata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kunth [= 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. W. Pohl" authorityYear="1990" baseAuthorityName="Kunth" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Nassella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Nassella mucronata" order="Poales" pageId="20" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mucronata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="109">Nassella mucronata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
] awns and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Beal" authorityYear="1896" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Bromus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bromus laciniatus" order="Poales" pageId="20" pageNumber="109" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="laciniatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="109">Bromus laciniatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Beal (= 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Bromus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bromus carinatus" order="Poales" pageId="20" pageNumber="109" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="carinatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="109">Bromus carinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hook &amp; Arn.) as determined by A.S. Hitchcock (isotype: US-A866077 fragm. ex P-Fourn-163!). Notes by A.S. Hitchcock on the US sheet with two fragment packets indicate that there are two species of 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Bromus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bromus" order="Poales" pageId="20" pageNumber="109" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="109">Bromus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the herb. Fournier sheet: A is 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. richardsonii" pageId="20" pageNumber="109" rank="species" species="richardsonii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="109">B. richardsonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Link; B is 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. carinatus" pageId="20" pageNumber="109" rank="species" species="carinatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="109">B. carinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, also annotated by ASH.
</paragraph>
